### Control Message Stream Lifecycle (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-typescript/blob/main/helpers.md

Offers methods to manage the lifecycle of a message stream. The abort() method cancels the stream and any network requests, while done() returns a promise that resolves when the stream completes. currentMessage provides the current state of the accumulated message.

```typescript
stream.abort()
await stream.done()
stream.currentMessage
```

