### Stream Message using Anthropic SDK Typescript

Source: https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-typescript/blob/main/api.md

This function streams message responses from the Anthropic API. It allows for real-time processing of the response as it's generated. The function returns a MessageStream object which can be iterated over.

```typescript
import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk';

const client = new Anthropic({ apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY' });

async function streamMessage() {
  const stream = await client.messages.stream({
    model: 'claude-3-opus-20240229',
    max_tokens: 1024,
    messages: [
      {
        role: 'user',
        content: 'Hello, Claude'
      }
    ]
  });

  for await (const event of stream) {
    if (event.type === 'contentBlockStart' || event.type === 'contentBlockDelta') {
      console.log(event.delta.text);
    }
  }
}
```

