### Handle MessageStream Events (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-typescript/blob/main/helpers.md

Provides handlers for various events emitted by the MessageStream, such as connection establishment, receiving stream events, text or JSON deltas, completion of messages or content blocks, errors, and stream abortion. The 'message' event signifies the completion of a streamed message.

```typescript
stream.on('connect', () => …)
stream.on('streamEvent', (event: MessageStreamEvent, snapshot: Message) => …)
stream.on('text', (textDelta: string, textSnapshot: string) => …)
stream.on('inputJson', (partialJson: string, jsonSnapshot: unknown) => …)
stream.on('message', (message: Message) => …)
stream.on('contentBlock', (content: ContentBlock) => …)
stream.on('finalMessage', (message: Message) => …)
stream.on('error', (error: AnthropicError) => …)
stream.on('abort', (error: APIUserAbortError) => …)
stream.on('end', () => …)
```

